---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import FinalCta from "@components/FinalCta.astro";
import { SITE } from "@data/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Why Practice Startup Services exists, who we serve, and how we work."
>
  <section class="border-b border-ink/8 py-16 lg:py-24 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 opacity-[0.04]" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <pattern id="bp-grid-about" x="0" y="0" width="48" height="48" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
            <path d="M 48 0 L 0 0 0 48" fill="none" stroke="#0E1F36" stroke-width="1" />
          </pattern>
        </defs>
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#bp-grid-about)" />
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="container-site relative">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-end">
        <div class="lg:col-span-9">
          <div class="phase-label text-bronze-700 mb-5">About us</div>
          <h1 class="font-display text-display-xl font-medium text-ink mb-5 text-balance">We help independent providers build practices that last.</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-12 max-w-prose-wide">
          <p class="text-lede text-graphite-700 text-pretty">
          Practice Startup Services exists because launching a private medical practice is one of the
          highest-stakes business decisions a clinician will ever make — and most clinicians get exactly
          zero training for it. We change that.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-ink/8 py-16 lg:py-20">
    <div class="container-site">
      <div class="prose-editorial">
        <h2>Why we do this.</h2>
        <p>
          The medical profession trains brilliant clinicians. It does not train business owners. The
          handoff from "I want to start a practice" to "I am open and billing" is where most clinicians
          get hit with the bill for that gap — in lost revenue from credentialing delays, working
          capital burned on the wrong systems, marketing money spent on programs that don't fit, and
          months of personal stress that didn't have to happen.
        </p>
        <p>
          We've watched enough practice launches succeed and fail to know that the difference is almost
          never talent. It's sequencing. The order of operations matters. Knowing what has to happen
          first, what can run in parallel, and what will cost you if you skip it — that's the whole game.
        </p>

        <h2>How we work.</h2>
        <p>
          We give the practical stuff away. Free phase guides. Free checklists. Free Medicare tools.
          We do that on purpose — the quality of our free content is the most honest signal you'll get
          for the quality of our paid work.
        </p>
        <p>
          When you want help with a specific phase, we have a build crew for each one: practice startup
          consulting, medical credentialing, revenue cycle management, medical practice websites, and
          practice infrastructure. You hire what you need, when you need it. We stay coordinated with
          the other crews — and your other vendors — so the build sequence holds.
        </p>

        <h2>Who we work with.</h2>
        <p>
          Physicians (MD/DO), nurse practitioners, physician assistants, behavioral health providers,
          and specialty practices launching independent or partner-owned operations. Solo, group,
          de novo, and post-employment transitions.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not work with PE-backed roll-ups, multi-site corporate launches, or hospital-owned
          subsidiary operations. Those are different animals with different needs.
        </p>

        <h2>What's different about us.</h2>
        <p>
          Most practice startup services are credentialing companies with a consulting page bolted on.
          We are the inverse: a launch advisory team that runs its own in-house credentialing, RCM,
          and website crews because those are the phases where the most expensive mistakes happen.
          You get strategy and execution from one coordinated team — not five vendors who don't talk
          to each other.
        </p>

        <p>
          When you want to talk, the first conversation is free. We will tell you whether you need us —
          and if you don't, we will tell you what to do anyway.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-8">
          <a href={SITE.scheduleUrl} class="btn-primary">
            {SITE.primaryCta}
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FinalCta />
</BaseLayout>
